text: Highland is an unincorporated community in Fillmore County, in the U.S. state of Minnesota. ==History== A post office was established at Highland in 1857, and remained in operation until it was discontinued in 1902. The community was named for its lofty elevation. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Fillmore County, Minnesota Category:1857 establishments in Minnesota Territory Category:Populated places established in 1857 Category:Unincorporated communities in Minnesota
title: Highland, Fillmore County, Minnesota
